headline: Why Food Companies Want Consumers to Buy More of Everything
summary: After years of raising prices, food companies making everything from cookies to snacks and frozen meals say they need to sell more products to post a profit.

headline: Two Reasons Why SJM is Risky and One Stock to Buy Instead
summary: J. M. Smucker currently trades at $106 per share and has shown little upside over the past six months, posting a small loss of 3.1%. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 4.7% gain during that period.
